#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Components/Server_to_Server_Protocol.rst:62
msgid ""
"``max-packet-waiting-time`` - this sets the maximum time for the packets "
"waiting for sending to some remote server. Sometimes, due to networking "
"problems or DNS problems it might be impossible to send message to remote"
" server right away. Establishing a new connection may take time or there "
"might be communication problems between servers or perhaps the remote "
"server is restarted. Tigase will try a few times to connect to the remote"
" server before giving up. This parameter specifies how long the packet is"
" waiting for sending before it is returned to the sender with an error. "
"The timeout is specified in seconds:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Components/Server_to_Server_Protocol.rst:70
msgid ""
"``max-inactivity-time`` - this parameters specifies the maximum s2s "
"connection inactivity time before it is closed. If a connection is not in"
" use for a long time, it doesn’t make sense to keep it open and tie "
"resources up. Tigase closes s2s connection after specified period of time"
" and reconnects when it is necessary. The timeout is specified in "
"seconds:"
msgstr ""

